1
00:00:31,980 --> 00:00:35,840
We hope you'll come back and visit us again and share the Lord with us.

2
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:38,980
I'm just so glad to be a part of family this morning.

3
00:00:39,460 --> 00:00:46,120
How many of you remember a show called Lifestyles of the Rich and Famous?

4
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:46,960
Do you remember this show?

5
00:00:47,850 --> 00:00:48,610
Is it still on?

6
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:49,900
It is?

7
00:00:50,580 --> 00:00:50,820
Yeah?

8
00:00:52,030 --> 00:00:52,830
Man, never quits.

9
00:00:53,820 --> 00:00:55,320
Somewhere in the world it's still on.

10
00:00:55,460 --> 00:01:01,620
If you recall, there was a gentleman by the name of Robin Leach, I recall, with a very funny voice.

11
00:01:02,670 --> 00:01:05,630
Lifestyles of the Rich and Famous, something like that.

12
00:01:06,630 --> 00:01:08,490
It's the best impersonation I could come up with.

13
00:01:08,490 --> 00:01:13,610
And essentially, this show was showing a certain class of people

14
00:01:13,610 --> 00:01:18,050
and how they live, where they go, what they buy, what they do.

15
00:01:18,690 --> 00:01:24,270
And we just, as consumers, desire to sort of live in a fantasy world for a half an hour

16
00:01:24,270 --> 00:01:28,630
to see this lifestyle that perhaps was just out of our reach.

17
00:01:30,750 --> 00:01:31,270
Lifestyle.

18
00:01:32,340 --> 00:01:33,840
We're fascinated by others' lifestyle.

19
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:34,620
What about our own?

20
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:35,780
What is a lifestyle?

21
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:38,720
A lifestyle is a person's pattern of living,

22
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:43,660
expressed in their activities, their interests, their opinions.

23
00:01:45,170 --> 00:01:47,970
And I ask you this morning, what kind of a lifestyle do you have?

24
00:01:48,190 --> 00:01:51,090
You may not relate to the lifestyles of the rich and famous.

25
00:01:51,170 --> 00:01:52,130
I certainly do not.

26
00:01:52,470 --> 00:01:55,850
I don't think many of us sail on our 50-foot yachts.

27
00:01:55,850 --> 00:01:57,510
I don't know that any of us has that.

28
00:01:57,510 --> 00:02:01,150
If you do, I'd like to go with you, but I don't think that's where we're at.

29
00:02:01,150 --> 00:02:08,370
But you might consider your lifestyle to be perhaps characterized by your calling in life, by your profession.

30
00:02:09,230 --> 00:02:16,150
You might see yourself as a student, and my lifestyle is a student lifestyle, or a soccer mom lifestyle.

31
00:02:17,110 --> 00:02:20,650
Some of you have children with the soccer mom, soccer dad lifestyle.

32
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:22,390
I fit into part of that.

33
00:02:22,850 --> 00:02:23,770
It's a crazy lifestyle.

34
00:02:25,060 --> 00:02:28,820
You might define it by a hobby or a sport that you are passionate about.

35
00:02:29,540 --> 00:02:34,400
You might have a martial arts lifestyle, or a gardening lifestyle, or surfing, or skiing,

36
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:35,320
or whatever it is.

37
00:02:35,340 --> 00:02:39,080
You define kind of the whole way you do life by that activity.

38
00:02:40,650 --> 00:02:42,710
You might even characterize it by your faith.

39
00:02:43,590 --> 00:02:47,070
You might say, I have a Christian lifestyle.

40
00:02:49,460 --> 00:02:53,590
Have you ever thought of your lifestyle, though, as one of worship?

41
00:02:53,590 --> 00:03:00,680
Do you see yourselves as, I live a lifestyle of worship?

42
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:03,680
It may not win you a spot on television.

43
00:03:04,460 --> 00:03:09,040
Robin Leach may not call you to investigate your worship lifestyle.

44
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:10,680
But you know what?

45
00:03:11,590 --> 00:03:15,290
It's far better and far more important than the lifestyles of the rich and famous.

46
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:20,860
Because a lifestyle of worship is a blessing to God and to others.

47
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:30,790
Is the worship lifestyle, is it only for those who sing and play music and lead worship up here?

48
00:03:30,790 --> 00:03:37,170
Or can we all characterize our lives and our lifestyles as one of worship?

49
00:03:38,820 --> 00:03:41,320
The Apostle Paul said this in Colossians chapter 3.

50
00:03:42,860 --> 00:03:43,080
He said,

51
00:04:02,320 --> 00:04:05,480
giving thanks to God the Father through him.

52
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:10,360
Let the word of Christ, it says, dwell in you richly.

53
00:04:11,210 --> 00:04:12,490
Teach and then sing.

54
00:04:13,210 --> 00:04:14,190
And notice what he says,

55
00:04:14,450 --> 00:04:19,190
and then whatever you do, do it in the name of the Lord Jesus.

56
00:04:20,670 --> 00:04:22,570
He's talking about a lifestyle.

57
00:04:23,450 --> 00:04:28,030
Paul is talking about whatever you do, do it to honor Christ.

58
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:31,890
That's a lifestyle of worship.

59
00:04:33,180 --> 00:04:37,180
He's challenging us to do this, to work unto the Lord.

60
00:04:38,340 --> 00:04:40,800
To study unto the Lord.

61
00:04:41,140 --> 00:04:44,120
To play unto the Lord.

62
00:04:45,060 --> 00:04:47,160
Give unto the Lord.

63
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:51,410
Raise your kids and your grandchildren unto the Lord.

64
00:04:52,380 --> 00:04:54,560
Talk with your friends unto the Lord.

65
00:04:54,860 --> 00:04:56,640
Run errands unto the Lord.

66
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:57,860
You get the idea.

67
00:04:58,460 --> 00:05:02,660
All that we do, do it unto Him.

68
00:05:04,870 --> 00:05:07,670
He's talking about a lifestyle of worship.

69
00:05:08,740 --> 00:05:11,680
As we come to the end of this worship series, the past three months,

70
00:05:11,740 --> 00:05:15,360
we've been looking at what it means to be living a lifestyle of worship

71
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:19,880
and how to really let God be the audience of our worship corporately here

72
00:05:19,880 --> 00:05:22,160
and also of our entire life.

73
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:25,680
For we are out to please the Lord.

74
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,180
He is the audience.

75
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,500
It's been said He's the audience of one.

76
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:33,660
We work and do everything to please our Lord.

77
00:05:33,660 --> 00:05:42,490
One of the great creeds in the early church in 1647 called the Westminster Shorter Catechism

78
00:05:42,490 --> 00:05:47,210
asked this question, what is the chief end of man or human beings?

79
00:05:47,390 --> 00:05:52,160
And the answer, to glorify God and to enjoy him forever.

80
00:05:54,260 --> 00:05:56,360
It's worship as a lifestyle.

81
00:05:58,580 --> 00:06:00,160
We don't often live this way though.

82
00:06:01,080 --> 00:06:05,920
You've heard us say it here before from Gordon Dahl's great insightful comment.

83
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:07,900
I'll say it again.

84
00:06:08,380 --> 00:06:11,260
Most middle class Americans tend to what?

85
00:06:11,340 --> 00:06:12,720
They worship their work.

86
00:06:13,860 --> 00:06:15,440
They work at their play.

87
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:18,240
And they play at their worship.

88
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:23,380
I'd like to challenge us to flip that around and think of it as instead,

89
00:06:23,380 --> 00:06:27,540
how about we tend to worship through our work?

90
00:06:29,250 --> 00:06:32,410
What if we were to work through our play?

91
00:06:33,050 --> 00:06:36,530
What we love to do, we actually do that for a living.

92
00:06:36,530 --> 00:06:39,730
And what if we were to play through our worship?

93
00:06:41,370 --> 00:06:43,470
It's a whole different way of doing life, wouldn't it?

94
00:06:45,710 --> 00:06:47,810
See, our meanings and our values get distorted.

95
00:06:49,320 --> 00:06:54,160
It's often been said our lifestyles resemble a cast of characters looking for a plot.

96
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:58,340
We've got to get our priorities right.

97
00:06:58,760 --> 00:07:01,420
We need to put God back on the throne.

98
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:07,820
We need to worship God first and foremost in our lives, in everything that we do.

99
00:07:07,820 --> 00:07:12,230
because from out of worship comes everything else.

100
00:07:13,370 --> 00:07:16,530
And that's been the theme we've been trying to work at throughout this series

101
00:07:16,530 --> 00:07:20,670
is that out of our obedience, out of our worship unto God,

102
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:24,750
giving Him everything, all the rest of life comes out.

103
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:28,550
We evangelize and share Christ to the lost

104
00:07:28,550 --> 00:07:31,310
that they might be saved by the blood of Jesus,

105
00:07:31,310 --> 00:07:34,330
that they might glorify God with their lives

106
00:07:34,330 --> 00:07:36,610
and join us as we glorify God.

107
00:07:36,610 --> 00:07:44,470
We disciple other believers that they might know what actions, attitudes, and words bring glory to God.

108
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:48,640
We visit the sick, the prisoners, the despondent.

109
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:54,100
We help the orphans, the addicted, the poor, because all these things glorify God.

110
00:07:55,840 --> 00:07:59,630
Everything we do as a church is to glorify God.

111
00:08:00,150 --> 00:08:02,090
It's to point to Him, to give Him praise.

112
00:08:02,090 --> 00:08:07,530
Everything we do as Christians is to give God glory and praise.

113
00:08:07,830 --> 00:08:12,870
Hebrews chapter 13 gives us this great challenge.

114
00:08:14,770 --> 00:08:21,280
Through him, let us continually offer a sacrifice of praise to God.

115
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:25,040
That is the fruit of lips that confess his name.

116
00:08:25,910 --> 00:08:33,110
Do not neglect to do good and to share what you have, for such sacrifices are pleasing to God.

117
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:39,140
The writer of Hebrews is challenging us to praise God with our lips

118
00:08:39,140 --> 00:08:42,220
and to praise God with our actions.

119
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:47,220
In essence, to live a lifestyle of worship.

120
00:08:48,620 --> 00:08:50,940
All of life becomes worship.

121
00:08:53,580 --> 00:08:55,740
Now, biblical praise we see here.

122
00:08:56,380 --> 00:08:58,320
A sacrifice of praise unto God.

123
00:08:58,580 --> 00:09:00,500
A biblical praise is a sacrifice.

124
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:03,360
It's something we owe and desire to offer to God

125
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:06,660
because of who He is and what He has done.

126
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:09,490
And it should cost us something.

127
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:11,180
It should cost us.

128
00:09:13,490 --> 00:09:20,300
There's a true story of a woman who called the consumer helpline at the Butterball Turkey Company.

129
00:09:21,950 --> 00:09:24,630
Just before Thanksgiving, she called the hotline and said,

130
00:09:24,630 --> 00:09:29,690
By the way, is it safe to eat a turkey that's been in the freezer for 25 years?

131
00:09:34,130 --> 00:09:43,080
And the man indicated, well, if it hasn't been thawed ever, it shouldn't present any danger.

132
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:47,880
but he said, but I can't imagine that after 25 years in the freezer

133
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:50,480
that the turkey would have much taste.

134
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:54,740
Well, she said, that's what I thought anyway.

135
00:09:55,340 --> 00:09:56,820
I'm going to donate it to the church.

136
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:03,640
That's cold, isn't it?

137
00:10:04,180 --> 00:10:07,470
But isn't that how it goes sometimes?

138
00:10:08,070 --> 00:10:12,420
We give to God the leftovers in our lives.

139
00:10:14,540 --> 00:10:20,040
We donate things to the church that we wouldn't be caught dead sitting in any longer, right?

140
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:30,070
Let me tell you this, youth groups are famous for absorbing all the things you would never have in your living room any longer.

141
00:10:30,980 --> 00:10:33,800
So we'll give it to Jesus and let the kids sit on it.

142
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:37,280
But let me say, friends, not in this church.

143
00:10:38,380 --> 00:10:39,520
We're here about excellence.

144
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:45,710
We're going to give God our first fruits, not the dregs of our leftovers.

145
00:10:47,660 --> 00:10:50,040
And I'm proud to say that we're turning a great corner there.

146
00:10:50,940 --> 00:10:52,820
But you know, we do the same thing with our offerings too.

147
00:10:52,820 --> 00:10:55,120
We give to God from our financial leftovers.

148
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:58,020
We give to God from the leftovers of our lives.

149
00:10:58,320 --> 00:11:01,360
We give Him the last fruits instead of the first.

150
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:05,380
We don't sacrifice much for God.

151
00:11:06,310 --> 00:11:08,630
Offerings that don't cost us aren't sacrifices.

152
00:11:09,950 --> 00:11:13,510
See, in the Old Testament, the people were to give God sacrifices and offerings

153
00:11:13,510 --> 00:11:16,770
from their crops and their livestock, the first fruits,

154
00:11:17,130 --> 00:11:21,140
to say thank you for your provision in my life.

155
00:11:21,660 --> 00:11:22,980
Thank you for your goodness.

156
00:11:22,980 --> 00:11:29,700
They also sacrificed animals to communicate the seriousness of our sin before God.

157
00:11:31,040 --> 00:11:32,840
And it was a bloody mess.

158
00:11:34,550 --> 00:11:40,630
And when you're slaying that animal, you realize this issue of sin before God is a serious deal.

159
00:11:41,090 --> 00:11:43,730
Because there has to be a death that there might be life.

160
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:50,480
In the New Testament, Jesus becomes that one sacrifice for us.

161
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:55,080
And now our sacrifices are no longer animals on the altar.

162
00:11:55,080 --> 00:12:01,540
Our sacrifices come in the form of our lives as an expression of thanksgiving for what God has done for us.

163
00:12:03,530 --> 00:12:10,250
And the author of Hebrews says we are to offer to God a sacrifice of praise and to do good

164
00:12:10,250 --> 00:12:13,770
and share what we have as sacrifices unto God.

165
00:12:15,060 --> 00:12:20,780
And these sacrifices should cost us something, for it costs Jesus his very life for our lives.

166
00:12:20,780 --> 00:12:28,230
And so I want to give you this morning four examples of what this looks like in practice.

167
00:12:28,810 --> 00:12:36,110
To give a sacrifice of praise, to give a sacrifice of our lives as lives of worship unto God.

168
00:12:36,210 --> 00:12:44,160
The first is, we worship as a lifestyle in our person, in our person.

169
00:12:45,160 --> 00:12:51,060
Someone has said, when one truly gives himself or herself to the Lord, all other giving becomes

170
00:12:51,060 --> 00:12:53,450
easy. Because you've already

171
00:12:53,450 --> 00:12:54,730
settled the first issue.

172
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:56,720
Who do you belong to?

173
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:01,290
It's to God. Romans chapter

174
00:13:01,290 --> 00:13:03,250
12 in the wonderful Phillips translation

175
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:04,290
says this.

176
00:13:05,510 --> 00:13:07,990
With eyes wide open to the mercies

177
00:13:07,990 --> 00:13:10,320
of God, I beg

178
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:12,120
you, my brothers, as an act

179
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,340
of intelligent worship,

180
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:15,600
to give your bodies

181
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:17,800
as a living sacrifice,

182
00:13:18,220 --> 00:13:19,480
consecrated to Him

183
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:21,560
and acceptable by Him.

184
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:24,280
Don't let the world around you

185
00:13:24,280 --> 00:13:31,580
squeeze you into its own mold but let god remold your minds from within so that you may prove in

186
00:13:31,580 --> 00:13:39,300
practice the plan of god for you is good meets all his demands and moves toward the goal of true

187
00:13:39,300 --> 00:13:52,560
maturity great verse offer your bodies as living sacrifice your body is the essence of what you've

188
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:58,400
got here on this earth. And from your body come the rest of our acts of worship. When we give our

189
00:13:58,400 --> 00:14:07,440
body, we're giving it all unto the Lord. For our entire life is to glorify God. If everything we do

190
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:13,820
and are and think and feel is to glorify Him, then we've got to give our whole self, our minds,

191
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:22,860
our wills, our bodies, everything. And that's what He asks. So we give God first in our person.

192
00:14:24,600 --> 00:14:26,280
We also give him in our purse.

193
00:14:28,430 --> 00:14:32,270
For many, giving God our bodies and minds and wills, that seems easy,

194
00:14:32,350 --> 00:14:36,110
but our purses, our wallets, now that's a different matter.

195
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:40,900
2 Corinthians, he says this.

196
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:42,720
Paul writes, chapter 8,

197
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:45,760
We want you to know, brothers and sisters,

198
00:14:46,580 --> 00:14:50,400
about the grace of God that has been granted to the churches of Macedonia.

199
00:14:51,260 --> 00:14:53,500
For during a severe ordeal of affliction,

200
00:14:53,660 --> 00:14:55,780
their abundant joy and their extreme poverty

201
00:14:55,780 --> 00:14:59,500
have overflowed in a wealth of generosity on their part.

202
00:15:00,420 --> 00:15:04,600
For, as I can testify, they voluntarily gave according to their means

203
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:07,160
and even beyond their means,

204
00:15:08,020 --> 00:15:12,300
begging us earnestly for the privilege of sharing in this ministry to the saints.

205
00:15:12,980 --> 00:15:15,520
And this, not merely as we expected,

206
00:15:16,240 --> 00:15:19,160
they gave themselves first to the Lord.

207
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:24,300
If God doesn't have your wallet or your purse,

208
00:15:25,540 --> 00:15:27,180
He doesn't really have you.

209
00:15:27,180 --> 00:15:32,720
because our purse and our wallet represents what we really believe and hold on to.

210
00:15:32,820 --> 00:15:35,620
It really shows who's first in our lives.

211
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:40,420
And if we're going to give God a lifestyle of worship and give him everything we are,

212
00:15:40,620 --> 00:15:43,980
we need to give him our purse and say, Lord, it's yours first.

213
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:47,420
And thank you for what you've given to me.

214
00:15:50,090 --> 00:15:51,970
As I said at the end of our service today,

215
00:15:52,470 --> 00:15:56,940
we're going to take our offerings this morning and our pledges for next year's giving.

216
00:15:58,200 --> 00:16:00,720
And I trust that you have spent some time before God

217
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:02,020
I'm really trusting.

218
00:16:02,100 --> 00:16:05,460
You spent some time saying, Lord, what would you have me give

219
00:16:05,460 --> 00:16:08,460
that I might stretch and honor you and trust you

220
00:16:08,460 --> 00:16:12,240
and make all of my giving part of a lifestyle of worship?

221
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:16,200
Lord, I want to acknowledge your goodness.

222
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:17,460
I want to put you first.

223
00:16:18,660 --> 00:16:20,980
So I give you right off the top my firstfruits

224
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:25,220
as an act of thanksgiving, an act of sacrifice, an act of worship.

225
00:16:27,150 --> 00:16:29,910
And I would hope that last week's presentation might challenge you

226
00:16:29,910 --> 00:16:31,550
if you're just getting started in giving,

227
00:16:31,550 --> 00:16:34,670
that this challenge to strive to tithe by fives,

228
00:16:34,910 --> 00:16:37,530
I pray that that would really become real in your life

229
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:40,860
and that God will take us to great heights as we give.

230
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,840
And I'd love to see our church be like the Corinthian church

231
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:45,840
where Paul says, you know what?

232
00:16:45,860 --> 00:16:46,740
You've given too much.

233
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:47,180
It's okay.

234
00:16:47,580 --> 00:16:47,900
Stop.

235
00:16:49,360 --> 00:16:50,120
Wouldn't that be fun?

236
00:16:51,100 --> 00:16:52,880
Here's your refund check on your giving.

237
00:16:52,980 --> 00:16:56,080
I would love to cut checks back to you

238
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:58,590
because it was just too much.

239
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:01,440
Wouldn't that be a great goal?

240
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:08,240
A lifestyle of worship, friends, means that God has our purse.

241
00:17:08,340 --> 00:17:11,500
We give him our bodies, and now we give him our purse and our wallets.

242
00:17:11,600 --> 00:17:14,330
Number three, we give him our praise.

243
00:17:16,580 --> 00:17:22,220
See, genuine, acceptable, God-honoring praise is praise that first begins with a grateful heart

244
00:17:22,220 --> 00:17:26,400
and moves to our lips that are full of joy.

245
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:32,990
I find it interesting that Jesus, in his earthly ministry, was always telling people,

246
00:17:32,990 --> 00:17:39,170
Now, after you've been healed, don't tell anybody because the mobs he knew would come.

247
00:17:39,710 --> 00:17:42,910
He was always telling people, don't tell anybody what just happened.

248
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:49,040
And yet, they were so grateful, so thankful for his movement in their lives, they couldn't help it.

249
00:17:49,240 --> 00:17:50,260
And they leaked it out.

250
00:17:51,360 --> 00:17:53,840
I'm not supposed to tell you, but that man healed me.

251
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:55,500
He set me free.

252
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:57,840
And the mobs, they came.

253
00:17:57,840 --> 00:18:03,230
In the church today, though, we stand up here and say,

254
00:18:03,350 --> 00:18:06,790
please say something about Jesus to the world.

255
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:09,400
We've got it backwards sometimes.

256
00:18:11,070 --> 00:18:13,710
But friends, I think part of it is because we forget,

257
00:18:14,250 --> 00:18:17,110
we forget what God has done.

258
00:18:18,510 --> 00:18:21,190
Because really grateful hearts cannot be silenced.

259
00:18:21,870 --> 00:18:26,010
Really grateful hearts just explode with gratitude.

260
00:18:26,870 --> 00:18:29,950
And sometimes we have to go back and remember what it was like

261
00:18:29,950 --> 00:18:32,410
before God saved us, what it was like

262
00:18:32,410 --> 00:18:34,190
to live in sin and muck

263
00:18:34,190 --> 00:18:36,570
and all of those things and to say, Lord, thank you

264
00:18:36,570 --> 00:18:38,470
that you delivered me from that

265
00:18:38,470 --> 00:18:40,570
and all the good things

266
00:18:40,570 --> 00:18:42,750
in my life. And when we reflect

267
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:44,550
on those and make that list,

268
00:18:46,580 --> 00:18:48,000
you can't silence

269
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,800
grateful hearts

270
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:50,520
and lips.

271
00:18:52,550 --> 00:18:54,710
It's my challenge to us that we be a people of

272
00:18:54,710 --> 00:18:56,750
praise because we remember again

273
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:58,670
what God has done.

274
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,540
Jesus said, for out of the abundance

275
00:19:01,540 --> 00:19:03,280
of the heart, the mouth speaks.

276
00:19:04,950 --> 00:19:06,330
And a lifestyle of worship

277
00:19:06,330 --> 00:19:08,170
means that we're continually

278
00:19:08,170 --> 00:19:10,290
giving God praise for what

279
00:19:10,290 --> 00:19:12,110
he has done and we remember

280
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:14,230
over and over what he's done in our lives.

281
00:19:15,790 --> 00:19:16,750
So we give him our praise.

282
00:19:16,870 --> 00:19:19,200
And finally, a lifestyle

283
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:21,460
of praise. We give God

284
00:19:21,460 --> 00:19:22,780
a sacrifice

285
00:19:22,780 --> 00:19:24,260
of performance.

286
00:19:25,460 --> 00:19:26,380
Of doing good.

287
00:19:27,060 --> 00:19:28,500
Of what we do in the world.

288
00:19:30,100 --> 00:19:31,220
Ephesians chapter 8.

289
00:19:31,220 --> 00:19:33,160
A famous verse for many of you.

290
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:41,600
for by grace you have been saved through faith and this not of your own doing it's the gift of god

291
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:48,920
not the result of work so that no one may boast for we are what he has made us created in christ

292
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:58,260
jesus for good works which god prepared beforehand to be our way of life saved us

293
00:19:58,260 --> 00:20:02,640
to bring the kingdom, saved us to do works

294
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:06,660
he's preordained before the foundation of the earth, saved us that we

295
00:20:06,660 --> 00:20:10,660
might live a life of gratitude in our lips and in our being

296
00:20:10,660 --> 00:20:16,540
and our doing. It starts in a grateful heart,

297
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:20,840
vocalized in singing on Sunday morning,

298
00:20:21,680 --> 00:20:25,440
in our own private worship times of offering praise to God.

299
00:20:25,440 --> 00:20:29,480
And its ultimate end, though, is not just in praise, it moves

300
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:31,900
into actions that glorify the Lord.

301
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:36,960
A lifestyle of worship begins with a word of thanks to God

302
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:37,940
at the beginning of the day

303
00:20:37,940 --> 00:20:42,060
and proceeds to a demeanor of holiness in our jobs.

304
00:20:43,790 --> 00:20:48,310
Pleasing praise unto God begins with a robust singing here on Sunday

305
00:20:48,310 --> 00:20:52,790
and then attention to word and prayer on a daily basis

306
00:20:52,790 --> 00:20:57,090
and then it sets off and flowers into a life of love and good works

307
00:20:57,090 --> 00:20:59,790
beyond the doors of this church.

308
00:20:59,790 --> 00:21:02,410
we don't keep it in here

309
00:21:02,410 --> 00:21:04,580
we spread it around

310
00:21:04,580 --> 00:21:07,400
because we are living a lifestyle

311
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:09,660
of praise

312
00:21:09,660 --> 00:21:14,520
so I conclude this morning

313
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:15,460
with these thoughts

314
00:21:15,460 --> 00:21:19,020
how is your praise doing

315
00:21:19,020 --> 00:21:21,470
is your lifestyle

316
00:21:21,470 --> 00:21:24,010
a lifestyle of praise

317
00:21:24,010 --> 00:21:26,180
is your lifestyle

318
00:21:26,180 --> 00:21:27,640
a lifestyle of worship

319
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:31,230
and if you're growing in that experience

320
00:21:31,230 --> 00:21:33,490
will you dedicate yourself in this coming year

321
00:21:33,490 --> 00:21:35,370
that more and more of your life

322
00:21:35,370 --> 00:21:39,290
would be lived unto God for His glory.

323
00:21:42,550 --> 00:21:45,510
You might ask, does your offering before God

324
00:21:45,510 --> 00:21:48,290
through yourself, does it cost you anything?

325
00:21:49,560 --> 00:21:50,560
Does it cost you anything?

326
00:21:53,080 --> 00:21:55,540
The next question is, what is your praise doing?

327
00:21:57,250 --> 00:22:00,450
Is it time to find a ministry that needs you,

328
00:22:00,510 --> 00:22:04,090
that needs your gifts, that desires to work with you

329
00:22:04,090 --> 00:22:07,610
as you plug in and live a lifestyle of praise unto God

330
00:22:07,610 --> 00:22:09,270
with the spiritual gifts He's given you?

331
00:22:13,140 --> 00:22:15,960
There is nothing insignificant in the kingdom of God.

332
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:20,080
Everything that is done for his glory is important.

333
00:22:21,530 --> 00:22:26,510
And he's gifted all of you for something or many things that are special unto God.

334
00:22:28,230 --> 00:22:31,190
And it's my hope and prayer that you will discover those.

335
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:38,370
And that you'll make your lifestyle, your actions, a lifestyle of praise and worship unto God.

336
00:22:38,370 --> 00:22:42,990
and it's my hope and prayer

337
00:22:42,990 --> 00:22:45,780
that this church become a place

338
00:22:45,780 --> 00:22:48,730
where everybody's involved in ministry

339
00:22:48,730 --> 00:22:52,230
everybody's involved in giving their total being unto God

340
00:22:52,230 --> 00:22:55,170
and the mercy rises so high

341
00:22:55,170 --> 00:22:56,650
it spills over outside

342
00:22:56,650 --> 00:23:00,220
and the community can't get enough

343
00:23:00,220 --> 00:23:01,320
of what God is doing here

344
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:05,830
but we have to be willing to give ourselves unto God

345
00:23:05,830 --> 00:23:07,970
and there might be some things

346
00:23:07,970 --> 00:23:09,350
we're holding back in our lives

347
00:23:09,350 --> 00:23:12,130
some closets and places we don't want the Spirit to go

348
00:23:12,130 --> 00:23:14,220
that hold us back.

349
00:23:17,100 --> 00:23:18,840
My prayer for you is the Spirit would come

350
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:21,850
and gently draw those things out

351
00:23:21,850 --> 00:23:23,390
that you might repent and give them away

352
00:23:23,390 --> 00:23:25,880
unto Him, for they went to the cross.

353
00:23:27,260 --> 00:23:28,160
That you might be free,

354
00:23:29,310 --> 00:23:31,310
free to live all of your life

355
00:23:31,310 --> 00:23:33,880
unto worship unto our Lord.

356
00:23:36,530 --> 00:23:39,330
And as a way for us to symbolize that this morning,

357
00:23:39,830 --> 00:23:42,020
we're going to take our offering

358
00:23:42,020 --> 00:23:42,980
in a little bit different way.

359
00:23:44,460 --> 00:23:46,240
For this offering now this morning

360
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:49,900
is going to be a total body kinesthetic experience

361
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:54,520
to symbolize your giving, your total being unto God

362
00:23:54,520 --> 00:23:55,840
as a lifestyle of worship.

363
00:23:58,610 --> 00:24:00,910
And so at this time, as we're going to sing a couple songs,

364
00:24:02,890 --> 00:24:05,070
we're going to have our ushers stand at the back

365
00:24:05,070 --> 00:24:06,270
and they're going to move forward.

366
00:24:08,260 --> 00:24:10,260
And we're going to dismiss you row by row.

367
00:24:11,340 --> 00:24:13,760
And we just ask that you come to the center aisle.

